INSERT INTO `smell` VALUES (18,'2015-05-26 13:31:07','<p>It takes rather long to migrate existing data after an update to the data model (database schema).<br/></p>','Database, flexibility','2016-02-03 09:22:03','Data migration problems','published','hm',0,2),(24,'2015-08-19 18:04:02','<p>An application is not able to react on variable requests or work load and therefore has high latency during peak times.</p>','scalability,performance,high volume of requests','2016-02-03 09:25:34','Scalability issue','published','hm',6,2),(25,'2015-09-29 14:20:39','<p><span>Your</span> application requires a lot of session attributes. The amount of attributes reaches the limit of the session store (e.g. a client side cookie (4093 Bytes)).</p>','session, state, attributes','2016-02-03 09:14:35','Large amount of session attributes','published','mh',1,1),(26,'2015-09-29 16:23:08','<p>Your application stores sensitive data in the session, which can be a significant security issue. Depending on whether or not the session is hold (or its data is transferred) on the client side.</p>','sensitive session data, security issue','2016-02-03 09:27:08','Sensitive session data','published','hh',1,4),(27,'2015-10-14 06:58:46','<p>Is it the case that a component has a complex interface to another component which makes changes difficult and makes it difficult for interface partners to program against it.</p>','soap,rest,complexity,interface','2016-02-03 09:00:58','Complex interface','published','hm',2,2),(28,'2015-10-14 07:28:24','<p>General performance loss. Means not only at peak times.</p>','performance loss','2016-01-06 11:17:34','Performance loss','published','hm',2,1),(31,'2015-11-03 09:57:49','<p><abbr>The component violates good OOAD and <abbr title=\"Component-Based Software Engineering\">CBSE</abbr> practices, e.g. single responsibility (see video: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BD9VaTiLMpM\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BD9VaTiLMpM</a>).</abbr></p>','Cohesion, Coupling, Single Responsibility','2016-02-03 09:19:13','Large number of component responsbilities and collaborations','published','mh',2,7),(32,'2015-11-04 09:27:05','<p>In a steady growing software system, different components most probably have different data access implementations.</p>','data access, dao','2015-12-09 09:13:01','Different data access implementations','published','hm',1,7),(33,'2015-11-04 09:36:48','<p>A software system or a single component collects its data from many data sources. E.g. different databases.</p>','data access, data store, data source','2015-12-09 09:13:20','Many different data sources','published','hm',1,2),(35,'2015-11-11 09:04:56','<p>It is the case that a component has a strong dependency to one or many other component(s). This can cause the problem, that changes or extinctions in one component have an unnecessary effect other components.</p>','tight coupling, strong dependency','2016-02-03 09:42:09','Unnecessary tight coupling','published','mm',4,3),(36,'2015-11-11 09:30:20','<p>Loose coupling has the following autonomy dimensions: platform autonomy, reference autonomy, time autonomy and Format (see book: Cloud Computing Patterns, Fehling).</p>','architecture principles, missing patterns','2016-02-03 09:54:31','Violation of architectural principles','published','mm',1,5),(37,'2015-11-11 09:32:21','<p>Is it the case that your application has many different interfaces to communicate with many other components.</p>','interfaces, communication channels','2016-01-05 08:28:58','Many communication channels','published','mm',1,2),(38,'2015-11-11 11:02:33','<p>It is the case that your application is communicating with a lot of other components using many different interfaces and maintaining them is complex.</p>','interfaces, complexity','2016-01-05 12:56:21','Many different interfaces','published','mm',1,2),(39,'2015-11-26 21:53:15','<p>If multiple components or system parts are running on the same hardware or even on separate hardware, one part can impair the rest of the system.</p>','bottleneck','2016-02-03 08:58:57','Bottleneck component','published','hh',3,1),(40,'2015-11-27 00:00:33','<p>A load balancer does not exist or is not working properly, which causes an imbalance of load to the available application instances.</p>','load balancing','2015-12-09 09:22:53','Uneven load balancing','published','mm',1,1),(41,'2015-12-06 22:44:17','<p>It is the case that you have too high costs for third party software in your system.</p>','costs,license','2016-02-03 09:10:20','High licenses costs','published','ll',1,1),(42,'2015-12-06 22:57:38','<p>Your system uses many middleware components which makes it difficult to configure, maintain and operate.</p>','complexity,middleware','2016-02-03 09:11:29','High system complexity due to excessive middleware usage','published','mm',2,2),(43,'2015-12-06 23:59:24','<p>The performance of your application has decreased or does not measure up to your expectations. </p>','poor performance','2015-12-09 09:15:33','Poor application performance','published','hm',1,1),(44,'2015-12-07 08:03:46','<p>An application or a whole software system is not able to fulfill multiple requests in a desired timeframe or is not able to process them in parallel.</p>','response times,latency,concurrent requests','2016-02-03 09:31:01','Slow response times for concurrent requests (latency)','published','hm',1,1),(45,'2015-12-07 08:10:47','<p>You have a strong hardware system (e.g. multicore system) but your application is still running slow and the capacity of your hardware is not fully utilized.</p>','hardware,bottleneck','2015-12-09 09:15:57','Hardware capabilities not maxed out (bottleneck)','published','mm',1,1),(46,'2015-12-07 08:15:42','<p>There are coming in more work requests than your system can process (maybe only in peek times as well as permanently).</p>','queuing','2016-02-03 09:36:31','Undesired queuing of incoming work requests','published','hm',1,1),(47,'2015-12-07 09:09:58','<p>You have large unit of works which need a lot of cpu power and are not parallelized (e.g. rendering processes).</p>','lack of performance,single thread','2016-02-03 09:12:27','Lack of performance with computationally intensive, single threaded applications','published','hm',1,1),(48,'2015-12-07 09:12:08','<p>The costs for your systems hardware are to high.</p>','costs,hardware','2016-01-07 18:36:56','High hardware costs','published','ll',1,1),(49,'2015-12-07 09:45:03','<p>It is the case that a component you use, is depending on old technology (e.g. interfaces, frameworks) which is not supported by newer components in your system anymore.</p>','compatibility','2016-02-03 09:32:25','Software compatibility not given anymore','published','hh',1,7),(50,'2015-12-07 09:50:44','<p>A third party software is faulty and has to be replaced with a bugfix version.</p>','misbehaviour,third party software,buggy','2015-12-07 09:50:44','Misbehaving third party software (buggy)','draft','hh',1,1),(51,'2015-12-07 10:28:21','<p>Is your application being locked due to concurrent operations. E.g. concurrent data access or two processes trying to call a critical (synchronized) program section.</p>','deadlocks,locking','2016-02-03 09:20:29','Locks/Deadlocks','published','hh',1,1),(52,'2016-01-06 08:37:07','<p>It is the case that your database queries have slow response times.</p>','slow queries, database','2016-02-03 09:30:14','Slow database query response times','published','mh',1,1),(53,'2016-01-06 09:55:03','<p>It is the case that analytical data queries (aggregations and table scans) are performing badly.</p>','analytical data processing, slow','2016-02-03 09:28:53','Slow analytical data processing','published','mh',1,1),(54,'2016-01-06 13:07:47','<p>It is hard to test a component due the difficulty to simulate an interface.</p>','interface simulation, modul testing','2016-02-03 09:03:18','Difficulty to simulate interface (testing)','published','mm',1,7),(55,'2016-01-06 16:53:43','<p>It is the case that an application can not keep up with a high transaction volume.</p>','low transaction, throughput','2016-01-06 17:00:03','Low transaction throughput','published','hm',1,1),(56,'2016-01-07 09:48:59','<p>Is your web application missing a function to provide PDF documents with current information.</p>','online formatting,functionality','2016-02-03 09:23:24','Missing online formatting functionality','published','ll',1,9),(57,'2016-01-07 16:14:46','<p>Is your system dependent on a third party product. </p>','third party vendor, dependency','2016-02-03 09:35:39','Third party vendor dependency','published','hm',1,3),(58,'2016-01-10 17:48:49','<p>Your web application server process is using a lightweight server framework (e.g. Netty) which does not perform well due to the increase of traffic in your system. </p>','web-application, standalone, scalability','2016-02-03 09:35:12','Standalone web-application does not scale well','published','hm',1,1),(62,'2016-01-29 10:25:46','<p>See this blog post for definition of ST vs. MT: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multitenancy\" target=\"_blank\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multitenancy</a><br/></p>','Cloud Computing','2016-02-03 09:27:55','Single tenancy design','draft','hh',1,8);
